{% if game_framework == 'pygame' %}- Target frame rate: {{ target_fps }} FPS{% endif %}

**Game Loop:**
{% if game_framework == 'pygame' %}- Manual loop in `Game.run()`: handle events, update state, draw frame, tick the clock{% elif game_framework == 'arcade' %}- Managed by `arcade.run()`, dispatching to `Game.on_update()` and `Game.on_draw()`{% elif game_framework == 'pyglet' %}- Managed by `pyglet.app.run()`, with `Game.update()` scheduled via `pyglet.clock.schedule_interval`{% elif game_framework == 'pgzero' %}- Managed by Pygame Zero's runtime, dispatching to the module-level `draw()`/`update()` hooks in `main.py`, which delegate to the `Game` instance{% endif %}

